Is it a dependent version of `Function.update_apply`?
See the golf I just pushed. It's `apply_update`.
In fact, it works inline, so I've dropped this lemma.

@urkud, I added this one to make the naming question slightly easier; `dfinsupp` was really a distraction, and the same underlying function works on pi types too.

I'm happy to split the pi and dfinsupp parts into separate PRs if that's useful.
It feels better to use the same order of variables in two sections.
Good catch, this was accidental.

I have trouble parsing this sentence.

Maybe

```suggestion
Given a family of indices `Îº` and a multilinear map `f p` for each way `p` to select one index from
each family, `dfinsuppFamily f` maps a family of finitely-supported functions (one for each index `Îº i`)
into a finitely-supported function on the selection families `Î  i, Îº i`.
```
Yes, that definitely helped me.
Idem
